<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Description (female).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Colour.</emphasis>
Body yellow (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Signiphora perpauca Girault, female A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D antenna E fore wing F hind wing." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362576" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
), head yellow except occiput with curved brown band along occipital carina (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Signiphora perpauca Girault, female A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D antenna E fore wing F hind wing." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362576" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Antenna with scape yellow and flagellum brown, apical half of clava distinctly darker (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Signiphora perpauca Girault, female A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D antenna E fore wing F hind wing." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362576" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
). Fore wing with dark band behind marginal vein that is proximally and distally diffusely delimited (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Signiphora perpauca Girault, female A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D antenna E fore wing F hind wing." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362576" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
), discal seta present. Mt8 in female transverse, without a medial incision.
</paragraph>
