<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Morphology.</emphasis>
Head 1.76 times as broad as frontovertex width (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Signiphora perpauca Girault, female A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D antenna E fore wing F hind wing." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362576" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
), frontovertex width 0.77 times length of clava, distance from mouth margin to facial ridge 0.57 times head height. Antenna with 3 anelli (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
), F1 0.4 times as long as broad, F2 0.8 times as long as broad, F3 subquadrate, clava about 6 times as long as broad and 1.7 times as long as scape length (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Signiphora perpauca Girault, female A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D antenna E fore wing F hind wing." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362576" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure7">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
), pedicel 0.77 times as long as scape length. Midlobe of mesoscutum with 2 setae on disc and anteriorly with 6 setae, scutellum with 6 setae along posterior margin. Fore wing 2.9 times as long as broad (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
), longest setae of marginal fringe 1.4 times as long as width of disc, seta M1 present, M2b absent. Midtibial spur subequal in length to corresponding basitarsus (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
), the latter 0.56 times as long as midtibia. Ovipositor 2.1 times as long as midtibia and 1.4 times as long as hind tibia.
</paragraph>
